{
  "stem": "19923.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 92.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it took me a long time to figure out what was the language spoken at home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- we must have spoken Yiddish because I do understand Yiddish and I could not have learned unless I spoke it at home.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I have no awareness of having spoken Yiddish because I spoke German.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I do know from my earliest times that I could converse in Yiddish and understand Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I think that Yiddish was spoken in the home, if not on a regular basis at least on a frequent basis.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had the usual trappings of a Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had the-- the pushke, which we are all familiar with.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's where you put the money.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my family always kept the-- a menorah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We always had the-- the trappings of a Jewish home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We learned Hebrew at an early age, except that the Hebrew learned was not to understand but was mostly for to-- to be able to perform the rituals, to say the [HEBREW] the-- the prayers.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we were never taught Hebrew with a sense of being able to learn the language.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was only for the purposes of davening, which means to pray.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I have never learned Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Although I can read and daven very fluently, I have never learned to understand what I am reading to this day.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's a sad commentary [BACKGROUND NOISE] of our life, but that was the way the Jewish people were in those days.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Hebrew was not taught in the sense of enlightenment.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was taught with a cat of nine tails, we call it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] When we went to cheder in those days, we-- we could see in the corner of our eye that there was that-- that [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
